-- Pirelli Tire Chief Gori Says Second-Quarter Sales Boosted by Weaker Euro
-- Marco Bertacche
-- 2010-06-24T10:25:11Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-24/pirelli-tire-chief-gori-says-second-quarter-sales-helped-by-weaker-euro.html

          
          
             Pirelli Tire Chief Executive Officer
Francesco Gori said the euro’s weakness against the dollar had a
“moderately positive” impact on the company’s second-quarter
sales. The impact will be greater in coming quarters if the
dollar remains at current levels, he said in an interview at a 
Milan conference.  
